Name: Nick Williams
AboutMe:
Open Source and shared knowledge are two important things to me, so I like to participate in the online community. I have a YouTube channel OSEE that presents tutorials for things like FPGAs, Microcontrollers and other embedded things. I am also active on Instructables, posting projects every now and then. Everything I post is usually available for others to use.

I am currently a SW Engineer at Continental for Long Range Radars in ADAS.

Some of my other interests are working out and eating well; cooking and baking; playing older video games; home furnishing.

My strongest domains are Hardware Design, MicroControllers and embedded software/systems.
